## PlantUML SVG and Dark Mode Support

PlantUML's generated SVG manages prefers-color-scheme:dark, which means it can adapt to the user's color scheme preference.

### Using Media Queries for Responsive Styling

PlantUML supports using @media (prefers-color-scheme:dark) in style blocks to define different styles for light and dark modes. An example implementation uses:
```
@startuml
<style>
document { backgroundColor: #EEE; }
element { backgroundColor: #F00; }
@media (prefers-color-scheme:dark) {
  document { backgroundColor: #222; }
  element { backgroundColor: #00F; }
}
</style>
Alice -> Bob
@enduml
```

However, this is currently only working for background color, and probably only in rectangles.

### Transparent Backgrounds

The transparent keyword can only be used for background of the image. There have been some issues with transparent backgrounds in SVG output, as downloaded SVGs may not preserve transparency as expected, and using dark theme on the online server produces white backgrounds instead of transparent.

### Dynamic Color Selection

PlantUML allows dynamic font color selection using the #? syntax, which automatically chooses between two colors based on the current background color to ensure optimal contrast and readability.


